cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.CC

This paper deals with an extension of Description Logics (DLs) to handle fuzzy, incomplete, indeterminate and inconsistent concepts. DLs are widely used in Artificial Intelligence (AI) and databases (DB), which makes cs.AI and cs.DB likely sub-categories. The paper also presents a constraint propagation calculus for reasoning, which is related to logic (cs.LO) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with concepts and reasoning, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG).
